COURSE REGISTRATION AND EVENT CALENDER:

1. Program :

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h3>Course Registration</h3>
<select id="courseSelect">
  <option>CS101 - Programming</option>
  <option>CS102 - Data Structures</option>
  <option>CS103 - DBMS</option>
</select>
<button onclick="addCourse()">Register</button>

<ul id="courseList"></ul>

<hr>

<h3>Event Calendar</h3>
<input type="date" id="eventDate">
<input type="text" id="eventTitle" placeholder="Event title">
<button onclick="addEvent()">Add Event</button>

<ul id="eventList"></ul>

<script>
function addCourse() {
  let c = document.getElementById("courseSelect").value;
  let li = document.createElement("li");
  li.textContent = c;
  document.getElementById("courseList").appendChild(li);
}

function addEvent() {
  let d = document.getElementById("eventDate").value;
  let t = document.getElementById("eventTitle").value;
  let li = document.createElement("li");
  li.textContent = d + " - " + t;
  document.getElementById("eventList").appendChild(li);
}
</script>

</body>
</html>





2.  How This Code Works
Course Registration Section

A <select> dropdown contains a list of courses.

The Register button calls the function addCourse().

This function creates a new <li> and appends it to the <ul id="courseList">.

This mimics simple course registration.

Event Calendar Section

A date input (<input type="date">)

A text input for event title

The Add Event button calls addEvent()

This adds a new <li> to <ul id="eventList">

This mimics storing events with date + title.



